import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'])
    ax.set_xlabel('cx')
    ax.set_ylabel('cy')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Points")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Names')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Name Frequency'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='cx', by='name', ax=ax)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between name and cx?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Cx')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Name', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
